00:59:13.110 --> 00:59:15.450
everything is equally out of tune.

00:59:15.450 --> 00:59:20.070
There, and we're just used to
it so that's, it sounds fine,

00:59:20.070 --> 00:59:23.410
but as far as how the frequencies
actually line up mathematically

00:59:23.410 --> 00:59:26.430
to each other, pretty much
everything is out of tune.

00:59:26.430 --> 00:59:29.380
And what they would do in
the seventeenth century

00:59:29.380 --> 00:59:32.510
and in earlier times, they
would change the distances,

00:59:32.510 --> 00:59:36.230
it was variable between
different half steps in the scale

00:59:36.230 --> 00:59:41.040
so that particular keys, you could
play on a keyboard instrument,

00:59:41.040 --> 00:59:44.270
particular keys were exactly
mathematically in tune.

00:59:44.270 --> 00:59:49.010
